18 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Electric facilities provider -- wildfire -- cause of action -- standard of
19 care -- damages. (1) The purpose of this section is to set statutory criteria governing the civil liability of an
20 electric facilities provider for wildfire-related claims. An electric facilities provider has an obligation to serve the
21 public, and a standard of strict liability may not be applied to an electric facilities provider as follows:
22 (a) in a cause of action alleging the electric facilities provider's electric facilities or electric
23 transmission and distribution activities caused wildfire-related damages; or
24 (b) in a cause of action alleging an electric facilities provider's wildfire mitigation activities
25 conducted in accordance with a wildfire mitigation plan caused damages.
26 (2) An electric facilities provider may be found civilly liable only under the provisions of this section,
27 and may not be found civilly liable under any other statute, theory of recovery, or common law claim, for
28 wildfire-related injury or damages arising from the electric facilities provider's electric facilities or electric
